user_location: of Randalls Wines and Spirits Manchester, Missouri
review_blob: Deep dark aroma. A perfect combination of roasted malt and hop heaven. 100 IBUs is no joke. Great beer. Founders knocks it outta the park again.
beer_name: Founders Dark Penance Imperial Black IPA

user_location: of Randalls Wines and Spirits Manchester, Missouri
review_blob: Good hoppy aroma, but almost sour smelling. Initial flavor was very sour hop. previous years the hops tasted grapefruity this year more orangey. Good stuff and definitely one heck of an accomplished brew for Schlafly.

user_location: of Randalls Wines and Spirits Manchester, Missouri
review_blob: As soon as I see this beer I buy it. Dark and full bodied, warming and malty. Chocolate and coffee make a great combination and a great oatmeal undertone create a beer with a full and lasting flavor.

user_location: of Randalls Wines and Spirits Manchester, Missouri
review_blob: Great session ipa. Light and crisp with easy bitter hop taste. Good alternative to a domestic brew but rather pricey

user_location: of Randalls Wines and Spirits Manchester, Missouri
review_blob: Probably my favorite marzen year in and year out. Well rounded, malty and amber. Such a beautiful oktoberfest.

user_location: of Randalls Wines and Spirits Manchester, Missouri
review_blob: As far as an American marzen style UCBC really stepped up to the plate and cranked one deep into center, great palate on this one. Good mix of maltyness and slight bitter from a light hopping.

user_location: of Randalls Wines and Spirits Manchester, Missouri
review_blob: Dark coffee color, spiced aroma. Good pumpkin flavor and heavy spice notes. Great stout love the cinnamon.

user_location: of Randalls Wines and Spirits Manchester, Missouri
review_blob: Bottles are slightly skunky but still classic marzen style malty sweetness. Mini kegs are the way to go. Super fresh and perfect pairing for the brats and kraut
